# API Integration — source is yabala-be

Source of truth: `/Users/yeasirarafat/projects/yabala-be` (Django).

Before adding or consuming an endpoint, check the matching Django app in
`yabala-be/apps/<domain>/`:

- `urls.py` — available routes
- `views.py` — logic, method, and permissions
- `serializers.py` — exact request/response shape

## Domains

`analytics`, `menu`, `order`, `payment`, `promotion`, `settings`, `user`.

## Rules

- Cross-check real usage in `yabala-fe` (its `actions/`, `redux/`, `hook/`, `lib/`)
  to see how the endpoint is actually called and what params it expects.
- Mirror the customer app's `services/api.ts` calling pattern (`publicApi` /
  `protectedApi`, token attachment, interceptors) and its error handling.
- Keep one service file per domain in `services/` and expose data via React Query
  hooks in `hooks/`, matching `ybala-customer-app` conventions.
